<p class="ft127" style="position:absolute;top:1210px;left:856px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft128" style="position:absolute;top:1224px;left:627px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1210" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft1210" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(E) Payment shall be made upon the first request from the First Party, without deducting </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:176px;white-space:nowrap">any commissions, taxes, or expenses and without the  need for  a judicial ruling, </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:176px;white-space:nowrap">arbitration or otherwise. </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(F) The First Party is entitled to confiscate and liquidate the Performance Bond in the </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:176px;white-space:nowrap">event that the Second Party breaches its obligations under this Contract, </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>3-2 </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Extension of the performance bond </b></p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">The First Party may request an extension of the validity period of the performance bond </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">if the reasons for this are available in accordance with the Contract terms. The First </p>
<p class="ft1214" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">Party shall send the extension request to the bank directly. The Second Party shall bear <br/>the costs of extending the bond. </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>3-3 </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Forfeiture of the performance bond </b></p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) The First Party has the right to forfeiture of performance bond provided by Second </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Party based on clear reasons related to the reasons for which the bond was </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">provided according to Contract terms and conditions </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) The request for forfeiture shall be addressed directly and explicitly to the bank, and </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">the bank shall respond to the request immediately </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) The First Party may forfeit the performance bond of the Second Party in the event </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">that it breaches its obligations under this Contract. </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:101px;white-space:nowrap"><b>4 </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Financial consideration and payment mechanism </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>4-1 </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Terms of payment of the financial consideration </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:576px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:576px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>(A)</b>The First Party pays the value of the Contract to the Second Party according to what </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">is stipulated in Appendix (8)</p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:597px;left:381px;white-space:nowrap"> (Drawings and Bill of Quantities &amp; Financial values) </p>
<p class="ft1214" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">and after deducting what is imposed on the Second Party in terms of fines, <br/>penalties, or other deductions under the provisions of this Contract. </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) The representative of the First Party reviews each invoice submitted to it by the </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Second Party and ensures that it confirms the specifications and quantities agreed </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">upon under the Contract. </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>(C) </b>The amounts due are paid according to an invoice submitted by the Second Party </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">to the First Party within sixty (60) days from the date of the First Party ’s approval of </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">the invoice after verifying that it meets all the legal justifications for payment. </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>(D) </b>The amounts paid to the Second Party shall not exceed the value of the Works that </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:818px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">have been completed, and the amounts paid to the Second Party in the last invoice </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">before final invoice shall not exceed 90% of the total value of the Contract if </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">applicable if there is a performance guarantee. </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>(E) </b>The Second Party shall submit monthly payment applications regardless of the </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">progress achieved if applicable.  </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>(F) </b>The First Party has the right to make any  corrections or amendments to any interim </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:950px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">invoice of the Second Party as a result of any errors that occurred in previous </p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:972px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">invoices that were approved or paid to the second party. </p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>4-2 </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Advance payment </b></p>
<p class="ft1212" style="position:absolute;top:1016px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1211" style="position:absolute;top:1016px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) The First Party may disburse an advance payment to the Second Party as shown in </p>
<p class="ft1215" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">(Contract data), in return for a bank guarantee issued by Saudi Bank ONLY of the <br/>same amount as the advance payment, provided that the bank guarantee shall be </p>
</div>
