<p class="ft26" style="position:absolute;top:1219px;left:785px;white-space:nowrap">الدمام  - ٣١٤٧١المملكة العربية السعودية</p>




<p class="ft137" style="position:absolute;top:1210px;left:856px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft138" style="position:absolute;top:1224px;left:627px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1310" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft1310" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">valid, unconditionally, and irrevocable until full refund of the payment, subject to </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">the general provisions of the guarantees mentioned in the Contract. </p>
<p class="ft1312" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) In the event that the advance payment is paid by the First Party to the Second Party, </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">it shall be paid after the Second Party submits the bank guarantee in accordance </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">with  paragraph  (A)  of  this  clause  (4-2)  (Advance  payment),  while  the  First  Party  </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">deducts the value of the advance payment from the dues of the Second Party from </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">the value of each invoice  with a percentage equal to the percentage of the advance </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">payment to the total Contract value, as of the first invoice. </p>
<p class="ft1312" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) The First Party may notify the bank issuing the guarantee directly - without the need </p>
<p class="ft1314" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">to  notify  the  Second  Party  or  obtain  its  approval  -  to  reduce  the  value  of  the <br/>guarantee  in  the  same  percentage  that  is  recovered  from  the  advance  payment, </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">according to the invoices on the deducting date. </p>
<p class="ft1312" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(D) Disbursing the advance payment is permissible and subject to the discretion of the </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">First Party and as determined by it. In the event of disbursing the advance payment, </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">it is permissible to divide it and disburse it to the Second Party in installments. </p>
<p class="ft1312" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>4-3 </b></p>
<p class="ft1312" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Invoices </b></p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) After completing a percentage of the work, the Second Party will quantify the part of </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">the work completed, match it with the approved bill of quantities, prepare a monthly </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">invoice, and submit it to the First Party. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B)  The  First  Party  is  committed  to  disbursing  the  Second  Party’s  entitlements  in </p>
<p class="ft1315" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">invoices, in accordance with the work completed and in accordance with the terms <br/>and  conditions  agreed  upon  in  the  Contract,  after  deducting  the  fines  or  other </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">deductions incurred by the Second Party. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) The Second Party shall submit an account statement with each invoice it issues in </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:642px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">accordance with the provisions of clause (4.1) (Terms of payment of the financial </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">consideration). The invoice shall include all the completed work. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(D) The First Party shall release the final invoice to the Second Party after the Works are </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">delivered and initially accepted by the First Party and all snag items are completed </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">and closed, and in case of the initial acceptance is partially, the initial acceptance </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">of the last required work shall be considered and is required before the final invoice. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">The  Second  Party  shall  submit  the  necessary  certificates  with  the  final  invoice, </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">including, but not limited to, the following certificates: </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:818px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:818px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  1. A work completion certificate issued to the Second Party by the First Party. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  2. A valid commercial registration certificate for the Second Party. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  3. A certificate from the Zakat, Tax and Customs Authority proving the payment of the </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Zakat or tax due. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  4.  A  certificate  from  the  General  Organization  for  Social  Insurance,  proving  the </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">registration of the Second Party in the organization and payment of insurance rights. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:950px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:950px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  5.  A  certificate  from  the  Ministry  of  Human  Resources  and  Social  Development, </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:972px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">proving the Second Party 's compliance with the Saudization requirements. </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  6. Any other related certificates or required (clearance declaration) by the First Party </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:1016px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">and OR the relevant authorities. </p>
<p class="ft1312" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>4-4 </b></p>
<p class="ft1312" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Taxes and Fees </b></p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:1059px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1311" style="position:absolute;top:1059px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) This Contract shall be governed to the regulations and orders related to taxes and </p>
