<p class="ft1511" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">this information, and it may also investigate the Second Party or its Subcontractor </p>
<p class="ft1513" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">with companies or other parties to ensure the extent of their commitment to their <br/>Contacts. </p>
<p class="ft1511" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1511" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(K) Cooperating with any third party appointed by the First Party and not obstructing the </p>
<p class="ft1511" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">work of any of the other Second Partys appointed by the First Party to carry out any </p>
<p class="ft1511" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">work not included in the Second Party to implement any Contract concluded by the </p>
<p class="ft1511" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">First Party that is related to or complementary to the Work, in a manner that does </p>
<p class="ft1511" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">not  conflict  with  the  Works  assigned  to  the  Second  Party.  This  includes </p>
