<p class="ft1810" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft1810" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">without prejudice to the right of the Second Party to claim its dues up to the date of </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">termination for the service provided and agreed by the First Party. </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) The First Party may, at its discretion, terminate the Contract or withdraw the Works </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">from the Second Party. The First Party may execute the remainder of the Works at </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">the  Second  Party’s  expense  and  may  also  confiscate  the  Performance  Bond, </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">without prejudice to its right to claim additional compensation for any damages, in </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">any of the following cases: </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  1. If the Second Party materially fails to perform the Works in accordance with the </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">terms of the Contract, the First Party’s requirements, or issued instructions, or if </p>
<p class="ft1814" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">the Second Party delays implementation to an extent that completion within the <br/>agreed timeframe is deemed unlikely by the First Party. In such cases, the First Party </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">shall provide  the Second Party with a  written warning of fifteen  (15) days before </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">termination. </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  2.  If  the  Second  Party,  directly  or  indirectly,  through  itself  or  others,  has  offered, </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">given, or promised money or any other benefit to obtain this Contract. Such actions </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">shall not exempt the Second Party from potential criminal liability. If this occurs, </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">the  First  Party  shall  also  have  the  right  to  terminate  any  other  agreements </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">concluded with the Second Party. </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  3.  If  the  Second  Party  becomes  bankrupt,  enters  into  composition  with  creditors, </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">makes  an  assignment  for  the  benefit  of  creditors,  goes  into  liquidation,  has  a </p>
<p class="ft1815" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">receiver appointed, or undergoes any similar procedure that adversely affects the <br/>execution of the Works. </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  4. If the Second Party abandons the Contract or engages a Subcontractor to execute </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">the Works without obtaining the prior written consent of the First Party. </p>
<p class="ft1812" style="position:absolute;top:648px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>7-3 </b></p>
<p class="ft1812" style="position:absolute;top:648px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Termination of the Contract due to force majeure </b></p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:670px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:670px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) The First Party may terminate the Contract due to force majeure by virtue of a </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:692px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">written notice sent to the Second Party, in the following two cases: </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:714px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:714px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  1. If the force majeure prevents the First Party from carrying out any of its </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:736px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">obligations under the Contract and the force majeure continues for more than </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:758px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">sixty (60) days. </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:780px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:780px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  2. If the force majeure prevents the Second Party from carrying out the services and </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:802px;left:174px;white-space:nowrap">any of its obligations under this Contract for a period of more than sixty (60) days. </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:824px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:824px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) In the event of termination of this Contract due to force majeure in accordance </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:846px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">with the provisions of paragraph (A) of this clause, this Contract shall be </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:868px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">considered terminated within the period indicated in the termination notice. </p>
<p class="ft1812" style="position:absolute;top:890px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>7-4 </b></p>
<p class="ft1812" style="position:absolute;top:890px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Obligations of the Second Party upon termination of the Contract </b></p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:912px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:912px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">In the event that the Contract is terminated in accordance with the provisions of this </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:934px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">clause (7) (Contract duration and termination), the Second Party shall do the following: </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:956px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:956px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) Cease and stop executing Works unless instructions have been issued in this </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:978px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">regard by the representative of the First Party to protect people or property or to </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:1000px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">ensure the safety of the executed Works. </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:1022px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:1022px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) Hand over all Contract documents, mechanical supplies, materials, and other </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:1044px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Works on the site to the First Party, which are owned by the First Party. </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:1066px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1811" style="position:absolute;top:1066px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) Remove all other supplies from the site except for safety reasons. </p>
<p class="ft1812" style="position:absolute;top:1088px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>7-5</b></p>
<p class="ft1812" style="position:absolute;top:1086px;left:118px;white-space:nowrap"><b>  Settlement with the Second Party in cases of Contract termination </b></p>
</div>
