<p class="ft26" style="position:absolute;top:1219px;left:785px;white-space:nowrap">الدمام  - ٣١٤٧١المملكة العربية السعودية</p>


<p class="ft197" style="position:absolute;top:1210px;left:856px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft198" style="position:absolute;top:1224px;left:627px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1910" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft1910" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">In the event that the Contract is terminated by the First Party in accordance with the </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">provisions of clause (7-2) (Termination of the Contract by the First Party), clause (7-3) </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(Termination of the Contract due to force majeure), then the First Party shall, after the </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">notice of termination of the Contract becomes effective, do the following: </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) Pay the Second Party for the accepted Works that have been implemented and their </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">conformity  with  the  specifications  contained  in  this  Contract  was  verified,  in </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">addition to the supplies and materials on the Site which are in good condition and </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">were approved by the First Party before the date of notification of termination of the </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Contract  and  recovering  the  remaining  balance  from  the  value  of  the  Advance </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Payment (if any). </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:334px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:334px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) Release the Advance Payment guarantee and performance bond, after making the </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">necessary settlements, unless the First Party confiscated the performance bond in </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">reference to clause (7-2) paragraph (B). </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C)  If  the  First  Party  terminates  the  Contract  based  on  a  recommendation  from  its </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">competent  committee,  it  is  permissible  for  the  First  Party  to  take  whatever </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">measures it deems appropriate to preserve its rights, such as seizing the Second </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Party’s  entitlements  until  the  final  accounting  is  conducted,  or  to  suspend  the </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">decision to terminate the Contract and continue to manage the Contract work itself </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">or through another contractor  at the expense of the Second Party, if he believes that </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">there is an benefit for the project in its continuation. </p>
<p class="ft1912" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>7-6 </b></p>
<p class="ft1912" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General provisions on termination </b></p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:576px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:576px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) These termination provisions provide exclusively for the cases in which the Contract </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">may be terminated. The party who deems that he is harmed by the breach of the </p>
<p class="ft1914" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">other  party  -  at  his  absolute  discretion  -  has  the  right  to  refer  the  dispute  in <br/>accordance  with  the  provisions  of  Article  (5)  (Applicable  Law  and  Dispute </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Resolution) of the main Contract agreement to protect his interests lawful and for </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">any  compensation  he  may  be  entitled  to  for  the  breach  (including  reasonable </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">expenses and costs incurred in doing so). </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) Termination of the Contract does not affect any rights or obligations of the parties </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">prior to the date of termination. </p>
<p class="ft1912" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:93px;white-space:nowrap"><b>7-7 </b></p>
<p class="ft1912" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Suspension of work </b></p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) (A) The First Party shall have the right to suspend the execution of the Works, in </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:818px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">whole or in part, by providing written notice to the Second Party. The notice shall </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">specify the commencement date of the suspension and, when applicable, the date </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">of resumption once the reasons for suspension have ceased. </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:163px;white-space:nowrap">1.  If the Works are fully suspended, the Second Party shall be granted an extension </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:190px;white-space:nowrap">of time equivalent to the full suspension period. </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:163px;white-space:nowrap">2.  If the suspension is partial, the Second Party shall be granted an extension of </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:950px;left:190px;white-space:nowrap">time proportionate to the impact of the suspended Works on the progress of the </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:972px;left:190px;white-space:nowrap">Project. Such an extension shall be based on a formal request for an extension </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:190px;white-space:nowrap">of time submitted by the Second Party. </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:1016px;left:163px;white-space:nowrap">3.  For every thirty (30) consecutive days of total suspension, the Second Party shall </p>
<p class="ft1915" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:190px;white-space:nowrap">be entitled to three (3) additional days for mobilization and preparation to resume <br/>the  Works.  However,  the  total  additional  mobilization  period  shall  not  exceed </p>
<p class="ft1911" style="position:absolute;top:1081px;left:190px;white-space:nowrap">forty-five (45) days. </p>
</div>
