<p class="ft218" style="position:absolute;top:1224px;left:627px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2110" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft2110" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">non-compliant Works within the stipulated period the First Party may engage </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">a third party to perform the necessary corrective measures in accordance </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">with the Withdrawal Procedures set out in Clause 16 (Work Withdrawal), at </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">the Second Party’s expense. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2112" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:101px;white-space:nowrap"><b>9 </b></p>
<p class="ft2112" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Rejection of Non-Compliant Materials, Equipment, and Works</b></p>
<p class="ft2113" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:648px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) The Second Party guarantees that all materials and equipment supplied under this </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">Contract: </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2115" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">1.  Conform to the specifications required in the Contract. <br/>2.  Are new, unused, and free from defects in design, manufacturing, construction, </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">or measurement. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">3.  Are  compatible  with  the  intended  purpose  of  the  Works  as  specified  in  the </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">Contract. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">4.  Comply with all applicable Saudi laws and regulations. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">The Second Party further guarantees that, upon expiry of the Defects Liability Period </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">stipulated  in  the  Contract  Data,  warranty  responsibility  shall  transfer  from  the </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Second Party to the supplier or local agent. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) All  materials  used,  whether  locally  sourced  or  imported,  shall  conform  to  the </p>
<p class="ft2116" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">standard specifications approved by the Saudi Standards, Metrology, and Quality <br/>Organization  (SASO)  or  other  relevant  authorities.  If  no  Saudi  standard </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">specifications  exist  for  a  material,  it  shall  conform  to  one  of  the  internationally </p>
<p class="ft2115" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">recognized standards as determined by the First Party’s designated authority. <br/>All materials shall be subject to testing as stipulated in the Contract specifications </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">or  as  deemed  necessary  by  the  First  Party  or  its  representative.  Testing  may  be </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">conducted at: </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">1.  The place of manufacture. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">2.  The work site. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">3.  Approved laboratories. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">Samples shall be taken by the Engineer or the Second Party in the presence of the </p>
<p class="ft2115" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">Engineer and in accordance with the specifications. The Second Party shall bear full <br/>responsibility for all testing costs throughout the implementation period until final </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">acceptance of the Works. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) The Second Party shall obtain prior approval from the First Party’s representative </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">for all materials and equipment included in the scope of work. However, such </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">approval shall not exempt or reduce the Second Party’s responsibility for </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">compliance with the Contract requirements. </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:950px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:950px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(D) If any inspection, measurement, or test reveals that materials, equipment, or Works </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:972px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">are defective or non-compliant with the Contract, the First Party’s representative </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">shall have the right to: </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:1016px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2116" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">1.  Reject the non-compliant materials, equipment, or Works. <br/>2.  Instruct  the  Second  Party  to  remove  and  replace,  at  its  own  expense,  any </p>
<p class="ft2111" style="position:absolute;top:1081px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">defective Works or portions thereof that do not meet Contract requirements. </p>
</div>
