<p class="ft26" style="position:absolute;top:1219px;left:785px;white-space:nowrap">الدمام  - ٣١٤٧١المملكة العربية السعودية</p>


<p class="ft227" style="position:absolute;top:1210px;left:856px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft228" style="position:absolute;top:1224px;left:627px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2210" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft2210" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">3.  Require  the  Second  Party  to  rectify  the  defects  within  a  mutually  agreed </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">timeframe, ensuring full compliance with the Contract specifications. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">The First Party shall issue a written notification specifying the reasons for rejection </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">or required rectification. The Second Party shall repair or replace the rejected </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">materials, equipment, or Works within the agreed timeframe. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(E) The  Second  Party  shall  deliver  materials  and  equipment  in  accordance  with  the </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">specifications approved by the First Party, as per the Contract terms, and during the </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">First Party’s working hours. The Second Party shall be responsible for full delivery, </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">including transportation and associated costs. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:171px;white-space:nowrap">Delivery shall not be considered complete until: </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:334px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">1.  The materials or equipment have been unloaded and stored in accordance </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:225px;white-space:nowrap">with the manufacturer’s recommendations. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:198px;white-space:nowrap">2.  A visual inspection is conducted by the First Party’s representative. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:178px;white-space:nowrap">The  First  Party  or  its  representative  issues  a  temporary  receipt  notification  for </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:178px;white-space:nowrap">materials or equipment requiring further examination. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">The date of issuance of the temporary receipt notification shall be final if the </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">materials or equipment are accepted. If rejected, the rejection decision shall </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">become effective immediately upon being signed by an Authorized Person. </p>
<p class="ft2212" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:96px;white-space:nowrap"><b>10 </b></p>
<p class="ft2212" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Modifications to Scope of Work </b></p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) The first party has the right to assign the second party to carry out any work related </p>
<p class="ft2214" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">to  the  Contract  work  and  with  the  same  terms,  specifications,  and  prices  of  the <br/>Contract, and the second party shall carry out these works without any objection on </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">its part. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) The First Party may issue change requests in writing to the Second Party that include </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:642px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">all the necessary information related to the change. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) The Second Party shall prepare its proposal regarding the change request and the </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">expected impact on the work implementation schedule. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(D)  If  the  First  Party  approves  the  Second  Party’s  proposal,  it  shall  issue  a  written </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">confirmation defining the approved change, its associated cost, and its impact on </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">the project schedule. The cumulative value of change orders shall not: </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2215" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">1. Increase the Contract value by more than fifteen percent (15%), or <br/>2. Decrease the Contract value by more than fifteen percent (15%), </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">If the cumulative value of change orders exceeds 15%, the Parties shall enter into </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">good-faith  negotiations  to  determine  appropriate  adjustments.  unless  otherwise </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:170px;white-space:nowrap">approved by the First Party. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(E)  The  Second  Party  shall  submit  a  revised  project  schedule  immediately  upon </p>
<p class="ft2215" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">receiving an approved variation or Contract amendment. The First Party shall review <br/>and  approve  the  revised  schedule,  which  shall  then  replace  the  latest  approved </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:972px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">baseline schedule. </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(F) The Second Party shall comply with all approved changes. However, if the Second </p>
<p class="ft2211" style="position:absolute;top:1016px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Party is unable to procure the necessary materials for implementing the change, or </p>
<p class="ft2214" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">if  the  cumulative  value  of  change  orders  exceeds  the  15%  limit  stated  in  Clause <br/>10(D), the Second Party shall promptly notify the First Party. </p>
