<p class="ft257" style="position:absolute;top:1210px;left:856px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft258" style="position:absolute;top:1224px;left:627px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2510" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft2510" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft2511" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:88px;white-space:nowrap"><b>11-4  Existing Site conditions </b></p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">The Second Party acknowledges that it has completed and studied all the information </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">before submitting its offers and that the prices included in its offers are sufficient to </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">cover all its obligations under the Contract and other matters necessary to complete </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">and carry out the work in a perfect and proper manner. </p>
<p class="ft2511" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:88px;white-space:nowrap"><b>11-5  Unforeseen Site Conditions </b></p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) If during the implementation of the Works, one of the hidden defects appeared in </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">the Site that the Second Party or an expert was not able to identify, then the Second </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Party shall, within a period of (10) ten days from the date of the appearance of the </p>
<p class="ft2515" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">hidden  defects,  notify  the  representative  of  the  First  Party  of  those  defects.  The <br/>Second Party, when requested to do so, shall prepare a report to be submitted to the </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">representative of the First Party, specifying precisely the defects that occurred in the </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Site or in the neighboring areas, provided that this report includes the proposals of </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">the Second Party to overcome the apparent defects, the time required to resume </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">work, and the estimated resulting additional Cost details (if any). </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) The First Party is not responsible for any additional costs claimed by the Second </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">Party if it fails to notify the First Party during the notification period mentioned in this </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">clause. </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) The Second Party shall, in the event of the emergence of a hidden defect, do its best </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">to prevent or reduce the losses resulting from it as much as possible. </p>
<p class="ft2511" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:88px;white-space:nowrap"><b>11-6  Inspection of Adjacent Property</b></p>
<p class="ft2513" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:402px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:406px;white-space:nowrap">– If applicable<b> </b></p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:576px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:576px;left:141px;white-space:nowrap">(A) The Second Party shall, before commencing the implementation of any demolition, </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">backfilling, consolidation, concrete stabilization, or any of the Works specified </p>
<p class="ft2515" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">under this Contract, inspect the property adjacent to the site and the tools and <br/>equipment therein. </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:141px;white-space:nowrap">(B) The neighboring property is inspected in the presence of the owner or its </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">representative whenever possible, and the inspection is carried out by all </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">appropriate means to determine the exact condition of the neighboring property </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">before starting work. </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:141px;white-space:nowrap">(C) Prior notice of such inspection shall be given to the First Party and the </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">representative of the First Party may attend the inspection upon his request, and a </p>
<p class="ft2515" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">copy of the documents and the inspection report that took place after being signed <br/>by the owner of the adjacent plot must be submitted to the representative of the </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">First Party, and this shall be done with each plot separately. The inspection, once </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">conducted, is not considered one of the reasons for exempting the Second Party </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">from damages or damages to neighboring properties if the Second Party causes </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">any such damage. </p>
<p class="ft2511" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:88px;white-space:nowrap"><b>11-7  Dimensional Verification and Installation Compliance</b></p>
<p class="ft2513" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:583px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:587px;white-space:nowrap">– If applicable<b> </b></p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:950px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:950px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A)  The  Second  Party  shall  appoint  a  specialist  before  starting  the  installation  of </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:972px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">dimensions, whose task is to inspect the dimensions according to the plans and </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">specifications and according to the original points, straights and reference clauses </p>
<p class="ft2512" style="position:absolute;top:1016px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">indicated in the Contract, which was provided to the Second Party  by the First Party </p>
<p class="ft2516" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:168px;white-space:nowrap">, as well as preparing a report in this regard, provided that a copy of it is delivered to <br/>the representative of the First Party . </p>
</div>
