<p class="ft3310" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft3310" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">issued by an insurer licensed to operate in Saudi Arabia and with a financial </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">strength rating acceptable to the First Party : </p>
<p class="ft3312" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:189px;white-space:nowrap">1.  All-Risks Insurance: The Second Party shall maintain insurance coverage for </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">the  full  value  of  the  Works,  equal  to  its  full  replacement  cost,  including </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">demolition, debris removal, professional fees, and profit. This insurance shall </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">cover any loss or damage for which the Second Party is responsible until the </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">expiration of the Contract. </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:189px;white-space:nowrap">2.  Equipment  Insurance:  The  Second  Party  shall  insure  its  equipment  for  an </p>
<p class="ft3314" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">amount not less than its full replacement value, including transportation and <br/>delivery  costs.  This  insurance  shall  remain  valid  during  the  transportation, </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">usage, and demobilization of each piece of equipment. </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:189px;white-space:nowrap">3.  Workers’  Compensation  and  Employee  Insurance:  The  Second  Party  shall </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">provide insurance coverage in compliance with the General Organization for </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">Social Insurance (GOSI) for work-related illnesses and injuries, covering all </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">claims and liabilities in accordance with applicable laws and regulations. This </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">insurance shall cover all accidents, including but not limited to cases of death </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">and  injury,  and  shall  be  issued  by  a  reputable  insurance  company  with </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">sufficient financial capability. The insured amount shall not be less than the </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">value specified in (Contract Data). </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:576px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:189px;white-space:nowrap">4.  Comprehensive  Third-Party  Liability  Insurance:  The  Second  Party  shall </p>
<p class="ft3314" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">provide  third-party  liability  insurance  in  the  amount  specified  in  (Contract <br/>Data)  for  each  incident  related  to  the  Works  under  the  general  liability </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:216px;white-space:nowrap">insurance policy. This insurance shall cover compensation for: </p>
<p class="ft3315" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:257px;white-space:nowrap">• Environmental damage. <br/>• Damage caused by the use of cranes and heavy equipment, including  </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:732px;left:271px;white-space:nowrap">injuries and fatalities. </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:754px;left:257px;white-space:nowrap">• Losses or damage to property and neighboring areas, regardless of the </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:777px;left:271px;white-space:nowrap">cause or responsible party. </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:799px;left:257px;white-space:nowrap">• All necessary compensation to restore affected areas to their original </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:823px;left:263px;white-space:nowrap">condition, where possible. </p>
<p class="ft3312" style="position:absolute;top:845px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:845px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B)  The    Second  Party  shall  ensure  that  all  required  insurance  policies  remain  valid </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:867px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">throughout the Contract period. The First Party shall have the right, at any time, to </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:888px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">request copies of insurance certificates or other proof of coverage. The Second Party </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:910px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">shall  immediately  notify  the  First  Party  of  any  event  that  may  affect  the  required </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:932px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">insurance coverage. The Second Party shall notify the First Party in writing at least </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:954px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">[30] days in advance if any required insurance policy is amended, canceled, or not </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:976px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">renewed. </p>
<p class="ft3312" style="position:absolute;top:998px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:998px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) The Second Party shall provide the representative of the First Party with a copy of </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:1020px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">the insurance policies that it issues or renews in accordance with the provisions of </p>
<p class="ft3316" style="position:absolute;top:1042px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">this Contract within five (5) working days from the date of its request. It shall, upon <br/>request, submit any documents requested by the representative of the First Party to </p>
<p class="ft3311" style="position:absolute;top:1086px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">prove the payment of the insurance premiums by the Second Party and any other </p>
</div>
