<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C) The Second Party shall not disclose data related to the First Party to any third party </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">without  the  prior  consent  of  the  First  Party  unless  this  is  required  to  do  so  in </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">accordance with the applicable law. </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(D)  After  the  completion  of  the  implementation  of  the  Contract  or  the  expiration  or </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">termination of the Contract, the Second Party shall stop using any of the data and </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">information of the First Party. </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(E)  The  Second  Party,  including  its  employees,  representatives,  Subcontractor  shall </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">take no photographs on or of the Airport Site without the prior written approval of the </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">First Party. This Clause does not prevent the Second Party from taking photographs </p>
<p class="ft3814" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">for the purpose of the Works progress and reporting, however, any pictures of the <br/>facilities and structures shall not be used externally for advertising purposes or for </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">any purpose without the prior approval of the First Party </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(F)The  Second  Party,  including  its  employees,  representatives,  Subcontractor,  shall </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">make no announcement or release any information concerning  this Contract,  the </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Airport, the Site, or any part thereof without prior written approval of the First Party, </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">either in the media, social media or elsewhere. </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(G) The Second Party shall inform the First Party immediately of any violation related to </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">confidential data and information and provide a detailed explanation of the violation, </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">the type of data that was hacked, the identity of the people affected by that and all </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">other important details. </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(H)  The  First  Party  or  its  authorized  representative  may  conduct  the  necessary </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:576px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">investigations in the event of a violation, determine the consequences thereof, and </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">make all efforts to prevent a recurrence of the violation in the future, in addition to </p>
<p class="ft3814" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">taking what is necessary to correct  the violation and avoid the  damages resulting <br/>from it. </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(I)  Notwithstanding  the  obligations  of  the  Second  Party,  its  employees  and </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Subcontractor’  employees  to  keep  the  aforementioned  data  confidential,  if  so </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">requested by the First Party and/or the Engineer, the Second Party further agrees to </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">require its employees to sign a nondisclosure agreement prior to performing any work </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">under the Contract Agreement. </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(J) The Second Party shall abide by all the basic requirements of cybersecurity in the </p>
<p class="ft3814" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Kingdom  and  the  regulations,  policies  and  instructions  related  to  cybersecurity <br/>issued by the First Party, and all cybersecurity requirements issued by the National </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Cybersecurity Authority or third parties. The Second Party shall immediately inform </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">the First Party in the event that it or third parties are exposed to cyber-attacks. </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:106px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(K)The Second Party shall conduct Screening or vetting for candidates of operational </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">systems and critical/privileged positions. The Second Party shall provide the result </p>
<p class="ft3814" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Security  screening  along  with  candidates  C.V  prior  of  any  employment  selection <br/>process on DACO systems. DACO has the rights to reject any of candidates without </p>
<p class="ft3811" style="position:absolute;top:972px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">providing the reason to Second Party. </p>
