<p class="ft3910" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:293px;white-space:nowrap"><b>General Ts &amp; Cs Contract</b></p>
<p class="ft3910" style="position:absolute;top:46px;left:278px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:115px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Subcontractor in relation to the proposed assigned scope of work shall be explained. </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:136px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">The Second Party 's Subcontract shall not be approved for more than forty percent </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:158px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">(40%) of the Contract. </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:180px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B)It is required to have all the necessary qualifications to carry out the Works with any </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:202px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Subcontractor, and the Subcontractor shall be licensed for this, and classified in the </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:224px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">field  and  to  the  degree  required  in  the  field  required  to  carry  out  the  Works  if  the </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Works are required to be classified. The Subcontractor may not Contract with any </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">other  Subcontractor  to  carry  out  the  services  Contracted  to  be  executed  in </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">accordance with the provisions of this clause (24-4) (Subcontracting). </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C)The Second Party declare that the First Party has the right to pay the dues of the sub-</p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:334px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">contactors with the Second Party as a deduction from the entitlements of the Second </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Party - if any - in the event of his failure or delay in disbursing their rights for the parts </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">they implemented of the Contract. This declaration does not constitute any liability </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">on the First Party towards the Second Party 's Subcontractor or any liability towards </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">any claims or disputes between the Second Party and its Subcontractor. </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(D)The approval to appoint a Subcontractor does not relieve the Second Party from any </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">of  its  obligations  in  this  Contract,  and  the  Second  Party  is  responsible  for  any </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:488px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">subcontracted works. </p>
<p class="ft3912" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"><b>24-5 </b></p>
<p class="ft3912" style="position:absolute;top:510px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap"><b>Assignment of Contract </b></p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:532px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(A) The Second Party shall not waive the Second Party part thereof to another contacting </p>
<p class="ft3914" style="position:absolute;top:554px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">party  except  after  obtaining  the  approval  of  the  Authorized  Person  from  the  First <br/>Party. However, the Second Party remains responsible to the First Party in solidarity </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:598px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">with the assignee when executing the Contract. </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:620px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B) In case the Second Party waive the Second Party part thereof without obtaining the </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:642px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">approval of the Authorized person from the First Party, the Second Party remains fully </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:664px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">responsible for all the consequences of this waiver, including, but not limited to: any </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:686px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">guarantees, damages or indemnities incurred by the Second Party to the First Party </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:708px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">in this aspect. </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:730px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C)Without prejudice to the provisions contained in Paragraph (A) of this Article, the </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:752px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">Second Party must, when assigning the Second Party any part of it to another Party, </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:774px;left:162px;white-space:nowrap">commit to the following: </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:796px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  1- Submitting a written request to the First Party specifying the reasons for the waiver </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:818px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">and disclosing any other Contracts that he had previously waived. The First Party </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:840px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">has the right to accept or reject that request without giving reasons. </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:862px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  2- The assignment must be in accordance with an agreement concluded between the </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:884px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">Second Party and the assigned party, clarifying their obligations towards the First </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:906px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">Party and all the details of the assigned work and the role of each of them towards </p>
<p class="ft3915" style="position:absolute;top:928px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">it,  provided  that  it  is  certified  by  the  Chamber  of  Commerce.  The  assignment <br/>agreement will not be effective unless it is approved by the Authorized person in </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:972px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">the First Party and his written approval thereof. </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:994px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  3- This waiver should not harm the project in any way, including, but not limited to </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:1016px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">implementing it at low prices or delaying its delivery to the First Party. </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"> </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:1038px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">  4- The assigned new party must meet the same conditions upon which the Contract </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:1059px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">with the Second Party was concluded and be classified in the field of the work at </p>
<p class="ft3911" style="position:absolute;top:1081px;left:180px;white-space:nowrap">the same level as the Second Party or higher and pass all technical evaluation and </p>
</div>
