<p class="ft4112" style="position:absolute;top:246px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(B)  In  addition  to  the  foregoing,  no  modifications,  additions,  or  extensions  to  this </p>
<p class="ft4112" style="position:absolute;top:268px;left:167px;white-space:nowrap">Contract,  or  exceeding  its  assigned  value,  and  other  things  that  may  be  done  or </p>
<p class="ft4112" style="position:absolute;top:290px;left:167px;white-space:nowrap">agreed upon by the representatives, shall become effective without the consent of </p>
<p class="ft4115" style="position:absolute;top:312px;left:167px;white-space:nowrap">the two Parties to this Contract, provided that a Contract amendment signed by the <br/>two Parties shall be issued to that effect. </p>
<p class="ft4111" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"><b> </b></p>
<p class="ft4112" style="position:absolute;top:356px;left:144px;white-space:nowrap">(C)  Any  approval,  audit,  certification,  examination,  inspection,  issuance  of  any </p>
<p class="ft4112" style="position:absolute;top:378px;left:167px;white-space:nowrap">instructions, notices, suggestions, or any similar action by the First Party, Engineer </p>
<p class="ft4112" style="position:absolute;top:400px;left:167px;white-space:nowrap">or any of their representatives does not relieve the Second Party of any responsibility </p>
<p class="ft4112" style="position:absolute;top:422px;left:167px;white-space:nowrap">it bears under the provisions of this Contract. Including his responsibility for errors </p>
<p class="ft4112" style="position:absolute;top:444px;left:167px;white-space:nowrap">or cases of non-compliance with the Contract terms. </p>
<p class="ft4113" style="position:absolute;top:466px;left:83px;white-space:nowrap"><b>24-13 </b></p>
